 Shell Shell Petroleum Development Company  Communities of Oil Mining Licence (OML) 25 in Akuku-Toru Local Council of Rivers State and Shell will on Monday, July 1, 2019 sign a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) to be facilitated by the Rivers State Government in the final resolution of their conflict. Secretary to Rivers State Government, Dr. Tammy Danagogo, who brokered the deal yesterday in Port Harcourt, has directed the Solicitor-General of the state to draft an MoU on the premise of the resolutions reached at the meeting. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .